# Driftara Video (`video-gallery`)

> Stub — authoritative agent rules live in `CLAUDE.md`, `AGENTS.md`,
> `.cursor/rules/*.mdc`, `.agent/PROJECT_GUIDE.md`.

## What this is

Electron + React + Vite desktop app for a **local video library** (SQLite, scan, thumbnails, ingest). Standalone — not the image-scoring gallery.

## Where to look first

- `CLAUDE.md` — orientation and key files.
- `AGENTS.md` — slash commands, boundaries, commands table.
- `.agent/PROJECT_GUIDE.md`, `.agent/SAFETY.md`, `.agent/COMMANDS.md`.
- `.cursor/rules/` — focused mdc rules.

## Core technologies

- React 19, TypeScript 5.9, Vite 7, Electron 31.
- **SQLite** in the Electron main process (`electron/db/provider.ts`).
- State: Zustand.
- Design: `@synthet/image-scoring-design` (sibling UI package).

## Key entry points

- `electron/main.ts` — IPC handlers
- `electron/preload.ts` — `contextBridge`
- `electron/db.ts`, `electron/db/provider.ts` — DB (main process only)
- `server/index.ts` — dev Express API
- `src/main.tsx` — renderer entry

## IPC pattern (required)

Main process owns DB and filesystem; renderer uses `window.electronAPI` only.

## Commands

- `npm run dev` — full dev stack
- `npm run dev:web` — without Electron
- `npm run build` / `npm run dist`
- `npx tsc --noEmit` — renderer
- `npx tsc -p electron/tsconfig.json --noEmit` — main process

## Hard rules

- **Never** add renderer-process DB or raw filesystem access.
- **Do not** modify `.git/config`.
- **Do not** commit `*.db`, thumbnails cache, or local secrets.
- Backlog: use the shared GitHub Project when the team requires it — see `.cursor/skills/backlog-queue/SKILL.md`.
